<dl class="row" style="font-size:x-large">
    <dt class="col-sm-3 list-group-item-info list-group-item">Application description</dt>
    <dd class="col-sm-9 list-group-item-info list-group-item">
        DumpApplic is a backup tape journaling application.
        The operator is responsible to add the tapes(bar codes) into the database using the program and specify for what backup type are used for.
    </dd>
    <dt class="col-sm-3 text-truncate list-group-item-success list-group-item">Tapes</dt>
    <dd class="col-sm-9 list-group-item-success list-group-item">In the Tapes section there is the option to add, edit, delete tapes.</dd>
    <dt class="col-sm-3 list-group-item-danger list-group-item">Settings</dt>
    <dd class="col-sm-9 list-group-item-danger list-group-item">In the backup settings section the operator has to setup the daily backup days and the end of the week backup day (the backup can be weekly, monthly(first selected day of the next month) and yearly).</dd>
    <dt class="col-sm-3 list-group-item-warning list-group-item">Calendar</dt>
    <dd class="col-sm-9 list-group-item-warning list-group-item">In the Calendar section users will be able to see the weekly and monthly backup dates accordingly with the settings which are made.</dd>
    <dt class="col-sm-3 list-group-item list-group-item-success">Daily Tapes</dt>
    <dd class="col-sm-9 list-group-item list-group-item-success">In the Daily Tapes section the algorithm will retrieve from the database daily backup tapes which are needed to be checked and inserted into the backup library.</dd>
    <dt class="col-sm-3 list-group-item list-group-item-info">History</dt>
    <dd class="col-sm-9 list-group-item-info list-group-item">In the history section all backup journal can be seen.</dd>
</dl>



